s0.description: You are meeting Pakistan Army Captain Tariq Osmani at an officer's club. You have previously been introduced to him at an official meeting, and this interaction comes a day before a formal engagement with Pakistani representatives. You were speaking with a group when you and Osmani began a conversation. Your objectives are to:

objectives.failDescription: Remember, when greeting a military counterpart, especially those older than you, don't refer to them by their first name. It is acceptable to greet your counterpart in English, but it’s worthwhile to learn to greet in the local language. Hugging is common between people of the same gender, but only after friendships are formed.
objectives.label: Greet appropriately.
objectives.passDescription: You greeted your counterpart appropriately. When greeting a military counterpart, especially those older than you, don't refer to them by their first name. It is acceptable to greet your counterpart in English, but it’s worthwhile to learn to greet in the local language. Hugging is common between people of the same gender, but only after friendships are formed.

objectives.failDescription: Remember that offering hospitality to guests is an important aspect of society in Pakistan,  and not accepting this gesture is an affront to most people. You should be gracious in accepting offers of tea and food.
objectives.label: Respond appropriately to offers of hospitality.
objectives.passDescription: You accepted your counterpart's offers of hospitality. Offering hospitality to guests is an important aspect of society in Pakistan, and not accepting this gesture is an affront to most people. Be gracious in accepting offers of tea and food.

objectives.failDescription: Remember that when making small talk, you should avoid asking about female family members or discussing religion or politics. Good small talk topics include common interests, recent travel experience, and positive comments.
objectives.label: Build rapport with appropriate small talk.
objectives.passDescription: You successfully made culturally appropriate small talk. Good small talk topics include common interests, recent travel experience, and positive comments . Avoid asking about female family members or discussing religion and politics.

objectives.failDescription: Remember that topics like ethnicity, national politics, and religion are especially sensitive in Pakistan. Avoid discussions about tensions with neighboring countries. Once you gain a trusted relationships, you may be able to cautiously discuss some sensitive topics.
objectives.label: Navigate sensitive topics appropriately.
objectives.passDescription: You successfully navigated a sensitive conversation. In Pakistan, it's best to avoid topics like ethnicity, national politics, religion, and tensions with neighboring countries. Once you gain a trusted relationships, you may be able to cautiously discuss some sensitive topics.

objectives.failDescription: Remember, Islam is a fundamental part of life in Pakistan and observant Muslims pray five times a day. If a counterpart interrupts a meeting to go pray, be respectful and don’t disturb them. Wait for them to return and continue your meeting as normal.
objectives.label: Respect your counterpart’s religious practices.
objectives.passDescription: You successfully demonstrated respect for religious practices. Islam is a fundamental part of life in Pakistan and observant Muslims pray five times a day. If a counterpart interrupts a meeting to go pray, be respectful and don’t disturb them. Wait for them to return and continue your meeting as normal.
